fields.name: 1966 Fender Telecaster, Sonic Blue
fields.description: Beautiful example of a player's grade vintage Telecaster. Rosewood fingerboard which has been refretted and is ready to play. Wear on neck is 100% natural. Professional refinish and relic job to match by Cardiff luthier Dave Dearnaley. Supplied with original hard case.

fields.name: C. 1955 Gibson LG1
fields.description: Rare Gibson example of this kind. Brought to the UK about seven years ago from a music store in White Rock, BC, Canada. A very well-worn, played and loved guitar. In good playing condition, sounding great but could be fully restored if desired.

fields.name: Fender Squier JV Stratocaster (1982-84), Sunburst
fields.description: Prime example of a player's grade JV Strat. All original with exception of the bridge and rear guard. Maple fingerboard. Plenty of life left in the frets.

fields.name: 1989 Takamine EN-10
fields.description: A lovely well-gigged acoustic dreadnought-shaped guitar with built-in pickup - a favorite amoungst sound engineers. Solid condtion all-around. Natural signs of age and us are all cosmetic.

fields.name: 1960s Gibson Discovered Tremolo Guitar Amp
fields.description: All original vintage Gibson Valve Amplifier. Fitted with modern 1 x 12 Eminence Speaker. Sounds clean as can be with fully functional vibrato.

fields.name: 1950s Fender Princeton
fields.description: This super rare 4 1/2 watt amp is the dream of any Fender Amp fan. In all original condition and ready for those vintage tones only a 1950s fender can offer

fields.name: 1950s Fender Champ
fields.description: The small but mighty Champ. Available here in all original condition. The best recording amp that money can buy.

fields.name: 1960s Hagstrom Acoustic
fields.description: This Swedish-made acoustic is based on the Gibson J45, and really punches above its weight. Hand made to perfection and offered in great players condition. Grab yourself a vintage acoustic without the huge pricetag!

fields.name: 1960s Hofner Violin Bass
fields.description: Collectors grade example of this iconic guitar made famous by Paul McCartney of the Beatles. In all original condition, set up and ready to play.

fields.name: 1960s Selmer Zodiac Twin 30
fields.description: Beast of a vintage amp. Fully restored as close as possible to the  original. Complete with crocodile skin tolex and magic eye! Beautiful tremolo system unique to this amp. In full working order.

fields.name: 1960 Wandre Tri Lam
fields.description: Possibly the weirdest guitar we have in the store! Unusual design featuring a plastic body and metal neck. Not the most comfortable guitar to play but more something to hang on the wall and marvel at. In all original collector grade condition.

fields.name: 1960s Yamaha FG-180
fields.description: The legendary Yamaha FG-180 red label. Spruce top and rosewood back and sides. This guitar has been well played over the years and bears the marks to show. Tones like none other.

fields.name: 1966 Fender Telecaster
fields.description: Sunburst. Showroom example of this iconic guitar. Ash body and rosewood veneer fingerboard. All original everything. Hardly ever played.

fields.name: 1971 Fender Vibro Champ
fields.description: Possibly the best sounding amp ever. More reliable than its 50s and 60s counterparts. Unusual model with built in tremolo. Sounds a dream. In all original condition with original footswitch.

fields.name: 1971 Marshall JTM45
fields.description: The icon of the British rock sound. In all original condition. Serviced with a new set of valves and ready to rock.

fields.name: 1973 Fender Telecaster
fields.description: Natural. This players grade guitar has had lots of modifications over the years but still plays great. If originality is not for you this is your guitar. Original finish stripped away and varnished. Routed in the bridge postion for a humbucker, now fitted with single coil seymor-duncan pickup.

fields.name: 1974 Fender Telecaster
fields.description: Olympic White. Offered in all original condition. Original finish has nicely aged from olympic white into a butterscotch blonde. An effect only time can have. Lovely guitar with Ash body and Maple fingerboard.

fields.name: 1960s Hofner Verythin
fields.description: Brilliant collectors condition example of a Hofner Verythin. Rare example featuring three pickups, rather than the usual two. Not known for their playability, but it really does look great.

fields.name: 1977 Fender Precision Bass
fields.description: Lake Placid Blue. In all original condition. Near collectors grade. Only minor cosmetic marks in the finish. Set up professionally and ready to play.

fields.name: 1980s Gibson Les Paul Studio
fields.description: Natural. Sound like Bob Marley with this versatile guitar. In great condition all round, set up nicely and ready to play.

fields.name: 1980s Tokai Les Paul
fields.description: Black. The japaneses answer to the Gibson Les Paul. Unparalleled build quality, all original and in great condition. Set up and ready to play.

fields.name: 1987 Fender Squier JV Presicion Bass
fields.description: The legendary Squier JV in all original collectors grade condition. Build from American parts in Fender Japan's new facory. These guitars are loved by musicians and collectors alike.

fields.name: 1983 Fender Squier JV Stratocaster
fields.description: The legendary Squier JV (Japanese Vintage) in all original collectors grade condition. Build from American parts in Fender Japans new factory. These guitars are loved by musicians and collectors alike.

fields.name: 2000s Epiphone Les Paul
fields.description: Old Black. This heavily modified Korean-made Les Paul Gold Top has been heavily modified to look and sound like Neil Youngs iconic Old Black. Featuring genuine bigsby, nickel plated P90 pickup cover, firebird mini humbucker in the bridge postion and custom made metal pick guard. Custom paint job and relic to match.

fields.name: 2000s Gibson ES335
fields.description: Cherry red. Play like Chuck Berry with this mint condition Gibson ES335. Professionally set up and ready to rock and roll.

fields.name: 2003 Ibanez Prestige
fields.description: Amazing example of this super strat. Paint job like no other. Set up with 9s as it should be. Low action, fast neck.

fields.name: 2000s Fender Telecaster MIM
fields.description: Olympic White. Solid guitar for those who may not want to splash out on the American counterpart. Great pickups, great playability and great sound. Offered in mint condition.

fields.name: 1973 Fender Telecaster
fields.description: Natural. This players grade guitar has had lots of modifications over the years but still plays great. If originality is not for you this is your guitar. Original finish stripped away and varnished. Routed in the bridge postion for a humbucker, now fitted with single coil seymor-duncan pickup.
